stuff I'm not doing right.

00:31:32.160 --> 00:31:33.215
You know, Jeff, you
didn't evaluate--

00:31:33.215 --> 00:31:34.151
I'm like, I got it.

00:31:34.151 --> 00:31:34.650
OK.

00:31:34.650 --> 00:31:36.300
We wear funny hats.

00:31:36.300 --> 00:31:39.085
We have medieval ceremonies,
the whole nine yards.

00:31:39.085 --> 00:31:41.460
So these people are going to
be in predictable situations

00:31:41.460 --> 00:31:43.290
where there's a lot of scale.

00:31:43.290 --> 00:31:44.610
And failure's not an option.

00:31:44.610 --> 00:31:46.109
So you're going to
see three things.

00:31:46.109 --> 00:31:49.140
Scale-- we're selling
a lot of something.

00:31:49.140 --> 00:31:50.510
We're going to see complexity.

00:31:50.510 --> 00:31:52.500
Think about Boeing
and the new 87th--

00:31:52.500 --> 00:31:53.970
has two million moving parts.

00:31:53.970 --> 00:31:56.100
And the whole notion
is if you send--

00:31:56.100 --> 00:31:58.290
you bring that down the
wrong way, it goes kaboom.

00:31:58.290 --> 00:31:59.100
Bad things happen.

00:31:59.100 --> 00:32:01.440
You operate the wrong way, you
send the young men and women

00:32:01.440 --> 00:32:02.040
off to combat.

00:32:02.040 --> 00:32:03.120
Bad things happen.

00:32:03.120 --> 00:32:05.670
Now, interestingly enough, my
