to partner with the opposite.

00:34:16.723 --> 00:34:18.139
So the first thing
I'm telling you

00:34:18.139 --> 00:34:21.139
is on a very personal level,
the person who makes you crazy

00:34:21.139 --> 00:34:24.170
is probably what's
missing in your ability

00:34:24.170 --> 00:34:25.880
to grow as a person
and your ability

00:34:25.880 --> 00:34:27.834
to add value to
the organization.

00:34:27.834 --> 00:34:29.000
Is everybody following this?

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:32.120
Number two, you have
to manage appropriately

00:34:32.120 --> 00:34:33.929
to the outcome you want.

00:34:33.929 --> 00:34:37.460
So if I want the engineer
outcome, I have to use process.

00:34:37.460 --> 00:34:38.630
It's complicated.

00:34:38.630 --> 00:34:40.429
If I want the
artist outcome, I'm

00:34:40.429 --> 00:34:42.030
going to change the gene pool.

00:34:42.030 --> 00:34:43.370
And I'm going to hedge.

00:34:43.370 --> 00:34:45.170
That's why startups
run the way they do,

00:34:45.170 --> 00:34:47.630
because they can't
compete on scope or scale.

00:34:47.630 --> 00:34:50.389
So the notion is I've got
a screwdriver, a hammer,

00:34:50.389 --> 00:34:51.389
a wrench, and a saw.

00:34:51.389 --> 00:34:52.440
They're great tools.

00:34:52.440 --> 00:34:53.790
They're not interchangeable.

00:34:53.790 --> 00:34:55.370
And that becomes
the first challenge.

00:34:55.370 --> 00:34:57.300
Now, we have to
encounter the other.

